<Author>tedhart
<Content>Great Location, Friendly Staff The Fiesta Americana hotel has a great location. If you are coming on business the price is right for a very average hotel. Definitely nothing to rave about here, but nothing done wrong either. The hotel is very dated, the TV worked rarely and I could not adjust the air conditioning in my room properly. I was shocked by how thin the towels were and the bar of soap was nearly microscopic. I was however thrilled to find a full service Starbucks just off the lower lobby. It became my oasis in between meetings.PS I checked out the Embassy Suites Mexico City - Reforma Hotel, MX - Exterior of Hotel Paseo de la Reforma #69 Colonia Tabacalera, M, Mexico which is just across the street. FAR NICER hotel and nearly the same price. FYI 
