<Author>RJM1London
<Content>Avoid At All Cost When we decided to visit Mexico for a fortnight. We stoped at this hotel for x4 nights in Mexico City, and then came back to it for x1 night, after spending x8 nights in Tulum near Cancun, before flying back to London, UK. All in all 5 nights at this Hotel.The hotel was booked by Trailfinders in London (travel agents) who have never ever dissappointed us. I was travelling with my baby daughter and wife, and had requested family friendly accomodation for our stay in Mexico City, and in Tulum.Keep in mind this hotel claims to be a 4 star. Where to begin, although child friendly (and by that I mean they provide high chairs in the restaurant), the facilities and service on offer at this hotel was abismal, lacking in choice, and far below the quality expected from this hotel. Our advice if you have to go to this hotel is...Do not make any phone calls as they are 8 times more expensive than buying a phone card (which I eventually did) and using a public phone. Plus they charged me for calls which never connected.Equally do not use room service (its rubbish), do not use their internet facility they charged us 50peso for 30 minutes, the cyber cafe's outside charge 5 peso for 30 minutes (so basically x10 mark up).Check your bills, as they tend to make a tonne of mistakes. And I leave the best for last. All hotels however many or little stars they may have you expect one thing, and that is that it is clean. Well I can guarantee that this hotel has an infestation (or plague your choice of adjective, as we couldn't think of a stronger adjective) of bed bugs, my wife and I were covered by bites, about the same time we were complaining (the day of our departure), they were changing all (and I mean all) the covers on our floor, and the next. The bathroom, was filthy and in serious need of some repair.All in all, if I were to use European standards, this hotel would not get a single star. It fails on hygiene, cost transparency (I am being diplomatic here), quality, variety, and service.Our advice, avoid it like you would a biblical plague. 
