<Content>Great location in financial district/Centro Historico June 19, 2006I just came from Mexico City yesterday from a four day holiday with a friend. The hotel is centrally located on a major street near the financial district and the old Centro Historico District. It is a great jumping point to all parts of the city. Overall, I was happy with my stay, but I must point out the good as well as the bad to be equitable and fair. The staff is quite knowledgeable, helpful, polite and bilingual. The service upon arrival, during and leaving was great. The hotel room and facilities were clean and tasteful but are beginning to show their age, but, still not a problem. The Food service is o.k. but servers seemed robotic and not helpful. Our bar service was bad. We entered one bar and were ignored by the bartender. So we went to the bar next door that had good service. The mattresses are hard or firm. I personally had a difficult time sleeping. If you like firm then it's o.k. If you travel for business this is a good place to be. The property does not have a pool. If you swim or have children this may be a factor to consider. I felt safe all the time I was there and would recommend this property taking into consideration price and what I just mentioned. 
