<Content>Very Good Location We chose the Fiesta Americana Hotel based on Trip Advisor information and were not disappointed at all. The service is excellent and we found that the concierge service was outstanding. They booked two tickets for us for a Sunday evening performance of the Ballet Folklorico on the spur of the moment and were able to attend without a problem. Taxi service was provided to and from the Palacio Belle Artes and was very reasonable and safe. The food in the buffet restaurant downstairs is excellent and the service is outstanding. Each room has a safe, which is very desireable. We could walk to many sights from this great location although we chose to catch tour bus (right in front of the hotel for 100 pesos a day per person). This tour bus is great service that takes in all parts of Mexico City. The hotel is just a tiny bit dated, but the rooms are very clean and the maid service is excellent. 
