<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Good hotel, friendly staff, good location I stayed here for several nights in late March. It is on Reforma, about equidistant from the historic center and the Zona Rosa area. There is no subway in the immediate vicinity but busses go up and down Reforma. There is a taxi stand on the premises but it is expensive. On the other hand, they are safe and the cars are comfortable.The hotel has changed hands a couple of times. It used to be the Crowne Plaza. I believe the Fiesta American chain is now working on some upgrades, which are needed. The common areas are better than average - lots of shiny marble, typical first class Mexico City decor. The dining rooms are nice and the business center very nice.The rooms themselves are slightly on the small side and quite standard. My only real complaint is the fact that the rooms are a bit worn. The furniture is on the old side and the bedspread was faded and frayed. They had just put in new lamps in my room, so I'm hoping other upgrades are on the way. The bathroom was also on the smallish side, also with older fixtures but very clean and completely serviceable. I ordered room service for breakfast a couple of times and it came quickly. The food is good, not great. For better meals you'll have to travel a bit because there are not a lot of restaurants in walking distance. There is a Wings and Sanborns nearby (both Mexican chain restaurants that have decent coffeeshop type food), as well as a few other hotels. One of the best nearby restaurants is at the Sheraton Centro Historico on Juarez - taking the hotel cab, it will be a $9.00 US cabride. The restaurant Cardenals, inside, is absolutely first rate - updated Mexican food in an elegant atmosphere. They also have a smaller Italian restaurant which I found very good. A big plus for me, as a single woman traveler, is that the staff is friendly and helpful and the hotel is very secure. The safes in the rooms are not large enough for a laptop and I inquired about this with the concierge. She told me not to worry so I didn't, and nothing was ever touched in my room (on the other hand, I'd simply prefer that the safe be able to accommodate my laptop).I got my room for $70 US with Hotwire, a bargain considering that at the reception desk, they advertise a $125 room rate. I'd probably stay here again, and definitely would if I knew they had freshened the room decor. 
